<HTML>

<HEAD><title>Letters to ATR -- ATR</title></HEAD>
<BODY Bgcolor=#FFFFFF><CENTER><a href="/atr/bar4.map"><img src="/atr/bar4.gif" ismap border="0"></a>  </CENTER>
<BOLD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3>
LETTERS</FONT></CENTER></BOLD>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="lett.gif">
<P>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
Flat Tax Alternative</FONT>
	Thank you for your prompt response to my request for information on the "flat tax" proposals.  It will help me answer and ask appropriate questions when dealing with neighbors, our local candidates, and radio talk show hosts.<P>
	Two reasons for my interest are:<P>
	1.  I am an American citizen paying taxes to a government which doesn't have a responsible attitude toward spending.<P>
	2.  I plan on starting a small home-based business and even though I am a bookkeeper, the tax laws are presently so confusing that I dread even thinking about April 15, 1996.<P>
	Your ideas are responsible and simplified.  I have contact with many people who would like to receive your "taxpayer action alerts."<P>

Penelope Knight
Karlstad, Minnesota

Editor's note:  Since this is the first issue of American Tax Reformer, we are printing here a few letters recently sent to staff in the Washington, D.C., office of Americans for Tax Reform.<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=2 WIDTH=40%>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Reduce Super Waste</FONT>
<P>
	I have just finished Martin Gross's book "A Call for Revolution" and have run across your organization in a list in the appendix.<P>
	I was one of the citizens convinced of Washington's inefficiencies and excesses long before I read Mr. Gross's book, but I am now inspired to advocate the idea of practical steps towards rationalization and reduction of the super wasteful spending of our seemingly irresponsible governments.  I would welcome and hope to participate in the advocacy of every suggestion Mr. Gross makes, and hope that your organization may provide a channel for that endeavor.  Please be so kind as to send me whatever information you disseminate about your organization and a list of activities.  I would also like a history of your efforts if  you have one or a list of publications which can educate me concerning your public record.<P>

Rockwell R. Blake
Plattsburgh, New York


<HR NOSHADE SIZE=2 WIDTH=40%>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Rock the House</FONT>
<P>

Grover Norquist's new book, <address>Rock the House</address>, is a lively, penetrating account of how the GOP triumphed last November, an election that dramatically underscored the desire of Americans for a fundamental break from the liberal/Beltway politics of the past 30 years.What helps make Norquist's chronicle so superb is that he was absolutely instrumental in helping bring about this positive, seismic shift.  Rarely has such a committed, brilliantly effective activist also possessed such a lively pen!<P>

Malcolm S. Forbes, Jr.
President and Chief Executive Officer
Editor-in-Chief
Forbes Magazine
New York, New York


<HR NOSHADE SIZE=2 WIDTH=40%>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Organize Expatriates in Japan
</FONT>
<P>


	I am currently an assistant English teacher working for Saga Prefecture in southern Japan.  I am interested in learning more about your organization as I am concerned about the state of our nation (U.S.A.) and our growing national debt.  I would like to know what I can do to influence Congress from abroad, and also if I can organize fellow U.S. expatriates here in Japan to do the same.<P>
     I look forward to receiving information and advice from your group.  Thank you and please keep up this important work.<P>

Judianne L. Rigazio
Saga-shi, Saga-ken, Japan



<HR NOSHADE SIZE=2 WIDTH=40%>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=+2>ANNUAL MEETING
</FONT>
<P>

	December 15, 1995 is the date for the Annual Meeting of Americans for Tax Reform (ATR).<P>
	Any member who wishes to nominate an individual to serve as a director of ATR should submit a nomination at least 60 days prior to that date.<P>
	As stated in the ATR bylaws, any nomination must be submitted in writing and signed by five nominators who are members in good standing of the association.<P>
	The nominee receiving the most votes of regular members voting shall be duly declared, elected, and installed as the regular-member class director.<P>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="/atr/bar.map"><img src="/atr/bar.gif" ismap border="0"></a> </CENTER>
