<HTML>
<TITLE>DR. STUART M. BUTLER -- Heritage </TITLE>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<H3>DR. STUART M. BUTLER</H3>

<HR>
<B>VICE PRESIDENT/DIRECTOR DOMESTIC POLICY STUDIES AND ROE INSTITUTE FOR ECONOMIC POLICY STUDIES
</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/butler2.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Co-author of "The Heritage Consumer Choice Health Plan" and <i>Out of the Poverty Trap: A Conservative Strategy for Welfare Reform</i>, and author of <i>Enterprise Zones: Greenlining the Inner Cities and Privatizing Federal Spending</i>, the British-born Dr. Butler directs Heritage's domestic and economic studies research team. An Adjunct Fellow at the National Center for Neighborhood Enterprise, he holds a Ph.D. in American economic history from St. Andrews University in Scotland.

